            </div>
            <div class="text">
              Evie Johnson is a salon owner, Certified Trichologist, platform stylist and educator trained under the most prestigious lines such as Vidal Sassoon, Pivot Point and Activia. Evie&apos;s expertise is also represented by prominent product lines such as Alberto Culver and Mizani. She is, hands down, a master of her craft. Evie holds the title of Master Stylist for Mizani's International Developmental Team. Specializing in hair shaping, coloring and treatment, Evie&apos;s creations can been seen and identified around the world. Simply and bluntly put she is on pace to be recognized as a global icon. 
              <br><br>
              You can find her work almost everywhere. Whether it&apos;s thumbing through pages of spreads in trendy hair magazines, or ad campaigns by your favorite hair product lines, Evie&apos;s work speaks for itself. She has also personally styled celebrity notables and industry recording artist clients such as Tasha Smith, Trey Songz, Laurie Ann Gibson, Chrisette Michelle, Debra L. Lee, and Deborah Cox just to name a few.
              <br><br>
              Although Evie runs a tight schedule at her salon with her favorite, every day clients, she makes time to share and educate her fellow beauty professionals with her cutting edge styling techniques as well as her latest hair shaping trends and custom hair units. Using skills she&apos;s acquired over the years, Evie educates beauty professionals on taking their careers to levels some thought they could only imagine achieving. Whether it be photo shoots, film, everyday women, or wanting to be the star of your next event Evie is the stylist for you and for the beauty industry professional wanting to take their career to that next level Evie is the educator for you.
            </div>
          </div> 

          <div class="bio" data-rel="edmonds" data-modal-class="sessions" data-width="620" data-animated="1">
            <div class="modal-header">
              <%= image_tag 'sessions/edmonds.png' %>
              <span class="name">Jamal Edmonds</span>
              <span class="company"><a href="#">Mizani</a></span>
              <span class="line">&nbsp;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="text">
              At an early age, native Washingtonian Jamal Edmonds was captivated by his passion for hair care. He steadfastly began his career with salon assistantships in the mid 1990s and earned a scholarship to attend the prestigious Bennett Career Institute (BCI). Jamal graduated in the top percentile of his class from BCI, obtaining a certification in management as well as his cosmetology license from District of Columbia Board of Cosmetology. He is the founder and co-owner of Salon Lamaj in Washington, D.C. 
              <br><br>
              For more than 10 years, Jamal&apos;s detailed artistry and precision have consistently created a buzz in the hair industry. Over the last several years, he was the recipient of countless Golden Scissors Awards such as &quot;Braider of the Year,&quot; &quot;Weave Master of the Year,&quot; and &quot;Male Stylist Overall Winner of the Year.&quot; In 2003, as the winner of the &quot;Celebrity Stylist Avalon Products&quot; contest, Jamal assisted celebrity hair stylists Neeko and Frederick Parnell during a photo shoot. And, throughout his career, Jamal&apos;s styling has been featured in countless hair magazines including: Sophisticates, Black Hair, Mazza International, Hype Hair, Style Q, Black Passion and Montage.
              <br><br>
              Jamal continues to maintain a solid clientele, providing his artistic ability and consultant services for training, wedding parties, proms, graduations and special events in Washington, D.C., as well as in cities across the United States, upon request. A master hair technician, Jamal&apos;s skillful hands continue to make a statement in the industry. He has provided his hair care expertise to the entertainment industry in the form of commercial print and runway. In 2003, Jamal was the hair stylist for a Zuri Sheer Beauty product advertisement. And, in 2006, he was the lead hair stylist for former MTV Vee Jay and television personality La La Vasquez&apos;s cover photo shoot in Montage magazine. In 2009 Jamal landed two (2) magazine covers for &quot;Orlando Style&quot; and &quot;LMH&quot; magazine as well as a full editorial spread in &quot;Zink!&quot; magazine. In 2011 Jamal joined the MIZANI design team as an educator and continues advanced education in cosmetology as he strives and continues to grow in this industry. 
              <br><br>
              In addition to sharing his talent with clientele, Jamal allots time in his active schedule for mentoring up and coming stylists with trendsetting hair techniques in the Washington Metropolitan area. He occasionally participates in charitable organizations by donating his hair care services to those who are less fortunate. 
              <br><br>
              Jamal Edmonds&apos; superb hair designs are preferred for consultations, hair care advertisements and print campaigns as well as by celebrities. Contact Jamal for revolutionary techniques and wearable art! 
            </div>
